00:16:57,933 --> 00:17:00,477
-Come on! Let's go!
-To the church!

255
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:04,732
Hey, hyung!

256
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:09,737
Oh no.

257
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,947
-Hey! Just wait a minute, Father!
-Father!

258
00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:14,491
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Not so fast.

259
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:16,785
Wait!
Why is the JIU stopping us?

260
00:17:19,121 --> 00:17:22,041
Look at them! They're like
lost little lambs, aren't they?

261
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,085
They should get the chance
to scream at God to save them.

262
00:17:25,669 --> 00:17:27,254
Right, Ms. Deputy Mayor?

263
00:17:28,422 --> 00:17:31,300
Captain Kang, your soldiers have
nothing better to do.

264
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:33,052
You should've provided security today.

265
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:36,096
Oh, right! You guys are out of bullets.

266
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:38,557
What are you doing?

267
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,267
Hurry Sister! Go to the Church!

268
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:44,146
Yun-sang. Have you made a decision yet?

269
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:45,147
Clock's ticking.

270
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:54,573
Will you get lost already?

271
00:17:58,952 --> 00:18:01,663
-They're hiding our money!
-Hyung, this is crazy!

272
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:05,084
-Let's go and see for ourselves!
-Seriously, why are you acting like this?

273
00:18:05,167 --> 00:18:08,212
-I'm asking you to stop!
-I wanna know where Father Baek has gone!

274
00:18:08,295 --> 00:18:10,547
Hyung! Please! Seriously, stop it!

275
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:13,592
Listen to me! Hold on!
Please, hold on. Let me--

276
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:34,071
Oh my God!

277
00:18:44,581 --> 00:18:45,833
How could this ha--

278
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:55,300
Wait.

279
00:18:56,009 --> 00:18:57,094
This can't be real.

280
00:19:01,098 --> 00:19:02,099
How could--

281
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:24,705
Father, was there anyone left
inside the church during the fire?

282
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:26,290
No.

283
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:29,042
Everyone was in the city square
for the mass.

284
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:31,086
There's no way anyone was inside.

285
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:33,797
Have you had
any short circuits recently?

286
00:19:35,048 --> 00:19:37,050
I doubt it. It doesn't seem very likely.

287
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:39,928
May I see the church's floor plan?

288
00:19:41,471 --> 00:19:42,723
Floor plan…

289
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:44,433
I'll bring it to you.

290
00:19:53,942 --> 00:19:55,611
See you around, Dr. Ha.

291
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:08,874
I don't think that voice
had anything to do with the JIU.

292
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:12,169
But why would anyone disrupt a memorial?

293
00:20:12,252 --> 00:20:14,796
Does anyone need a reason?

294
00:20:15,422 --> 00:20:17,341
Hmm?

295
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:20,219
The world is ending.

296
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:23,096
Nobody cares.

297
00:20:26,099 --> 00:20:28,268
No one cares when we're all gonna die.

298
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:42,783
-He's so cute!
-Doggie!

299
00:20:42,866 --> 00:20:44,743
I can't believe
they burned the church.

300
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:47,829
At least they got the fire
under control quickly.

301
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:48,914
Huge cheeks!

302
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:50,832
-That's a relief.
-But still…

303
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:52,417
-So-min.
-What's his name?

304
00:20:52,501 --> 00:20:55,045
Take Hae-chan and Woo-chan home.
I'll be there soon, okay?

305
00:20:55,128 --> 00:20:56,004
Thanks.

306
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,923
-The kids wanna stay with you.
-What?

307
00:20:58,006 --> 00:21:00,217
-We'll be nearby.
-All right.

308
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,969
-Wanna go to the playground?
-Yeah!

309
00:21:02,052 --> 00:21:04,972
-Let's go. To the playground.
-To the playground! Let's go!

310
00:21:05,055 --> 00:21:07,599
-Should we go on the swings…
-Don't go too far away now.

311
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:09,893
-Okay.
-So-min, kids, be careful.

312
00:21:09,977 --> 00:21:11,895
-I wanna ride on the swings first!
-Okay.

313
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:13,689
-The swings, huh?
-Yeah.

314
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:16,441
Should I push you?

315
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:18,902
Yeah, I wanna swing high!

316
00:21:18,986 --> 00:21:21,530
-Let's hurry up, then!
-It's fine. They'll be all right.

317
00:21:21,613 --> 00:21:23,740
They're small enough
that they don't attract attention.

318
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:26,076
They'll be safe.
You don't have to worry about it.

319
00:21:31,164 --> 00:21:32,124
Hey, you know…

320
00:21:34,876 --> 00:21:37,629
…I said some things during confession
I shouldn't have.

321
00:21:38,797 --> 00:21:40,549
I'm afraid I'll be suspected.

322
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:43,844
I just said how I wish sometimes

323
00:21:43,927 --> 00:21:46,471
I could get the money back
I gave the church in donations.

324
00:21:46,555 --> 00:21:50,309
Do you think I sounded like
I wanted to burn the place down, huh?

325
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:53,228
-Actually--
-You think it does, hmm?

326
00:21:56,064 --> 00:21:58,650
I… I said something similar too.

327
00:21:58,734 --> 00:22:00,902
Huh? Wait, really?

328
00:22:00,986 --> 00:22:04,156
You think there'll be a lot of people
trying to get their money back, then?

329
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:07,451
I think after this fire,
it'll all get swept under the rug.

330
00:22:07,534 --> 00:22:09,661
Well, not if I have
anything to say about it.

331
00:22:21,298 --> 00:22:22,174
Ow!

332
00:22:22,257 --> 00:22:24,676
I almost died of embarrassment
because of my dad.

333
00:22:25,177 --> 00:22:27,054
My mom
is probably still in shock.

334
00:22:28,013 --> 00:22:30,015
It burned even before the asteroid hit.

335
00:22:30,932 --> 00:22:33,018
So, I guess it's just
burning a little earlier.

336
00:22:33,101 --> 00:22:35,812
Yeah. When it hits,
everything's gonna burn anyway.

337
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:40,317
-Is Sister Regina okay?
-Oh! There's Jin-seo. Let's go.

338
00:22:40,817 --> 00:22:41,777
Sure.

339
00:22:43,612 --> 00:22:46,448
You have to be
extra careful today, okay? Be safe.

340
00:22:46,531 --> 00:22:47,407
Okay.

341
00:22:51,703 --> 00:22:53,455
I can't believe this happened.

342
00:22:54,706 --> 00:22:56,833
How could they do this to a church?

343
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:02,422
It looks like
all organizations are the same.

344
00:23:04,883 --> 00:23:08,220
Young-ji, did something like this
happen before?

345
00:23:16,478 --> 00:23:17,771
Shine the light here.

346
00:23:58,728 --> 00:24:00,981
You idiot! How could you
set the church on fire?

347
00:24:01,064 --> 00:24:03,108
So?
The place was empty. 

348
00:24:03,191 --> 00:24:05,152
And nobody got hurt. 

349
00:24:06,736 --> 00:24:10,365
If we want to give people money to escape,
the vault door needs to be opened.

350
00:24:10,449 --> 00:24:11,450
Shut up!

351
00:24:24,045 --> 00:24:25,839
What's this?

352
00:24:25,922 --> 00:24:29,634
Father Baek's storage room.
We don't have a key or know the passcode.

353
00:24:30,302 --> 00:24:32,929
We have to check in there
as well. Can we open it?

354
00:24:33,013 --> 00:24:35,932
-No, this is--
-Sure, sure! Go right ahead.

355
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:37,893
-Open it.
-Hmm.

356
00:25:06,922 --> 00:25:07,923
Sister.

357
00:25:12,093 --> 00:25:13,261
This can't be.

358
00:25:14,179 --> 00:25:16,932
The door is fireproof.
Everything inside is fine.

359
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:26,274
It seems the cause
was a faulty circuit breaker.

360
00:25:27,317 --> 00:25:30,153
Luckily, there seems to be
no structural integrity issues,

361
00:25:30,237 --> 00:25:33,281
but there could still be
live embers tucked away.

362
00:25:33,365 --> 00:25:34,741
Be on the lookout for those.

363
00:25:34,824 --> 00:25:37,452
What did they say?
It's probably not arson?

364
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:38,870
I don't know what to think.

365
00:25:39,371 --> 00:25:42,040
Oh, no. Who would set a church on fire?

366
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:45,460
Goodness, my heart is still pounding.

367
00:25:46,169 --> 00:25:47,045
Oh.

368
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:49,422
When Namdaemun Gate burned down,

369
00:25:49,506 --> 00:25:52,467
at first,
they said it was an accident too.

370
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:54,511
Ah! You'd think people would know

371
00:25:54,594 --> 00:25:57,597
setting a church on fire
is a one-way ticket to hell.

372
00:25:57,681 --> 00:25:59,683
That's some imagination
you two have got there.

373
00:25:59,766 --> 00:26:02,769
Reality is stranger than fiction, my dear.

374
00:26:04,729 --> 00:26:05,772
That's true.

375
00:26:06,523 --> 00:26:07,649
That's true.

376
00:26:08,525 --> 00:26:10,360
I didn't think it'd be empty though.

377
00:26:13,196 --> 00:26:14,030
What?

378
00:26:15,282 --> 00:26:16,992
-Huh?
-What do you mean?

379
00:26:18,076 --> 00:26:20,203
The safe was empty?
So where's all that gold?

380
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:24,124
-Father!
-Oh my, Father!

381
00:26:24,207 --> 00:26:25,542
-Is he all right?
-Father!

382
00:26:26,042 --> 00:26:27,669
-Goodness. What do we do?
-Oh my!

383
00:26:29,629 --> 00:26:32,299
Was this all the equipment
used during the memorial?

384
00:26:32,382 --> 00:26:33,550
Uh-huh.

385
00:26:33,633 --> 00:26:36,970
So, besides…
all the staff working at city hall

386
00:26:37,053 --> 00:26:39,139
and today's vendors,
did anyone else help?

387
00:26:39,222 --> 00:26:40,056
Take this.

388
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:42,434
-Any volunteers or outside groups?
-Not ours.

389
00:26:42,517 --> 00:26:44,644
-Wait, this isn't yours?
-No, it's not.

390
00:26:45,478 --> 00:26:48,773
-And this isn't the city's either?
-Yeah, that one's not ours.

391
00:26:48,857 --> 00:26:49,941
-Wait, what?
-Here.

392
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:52,110
Does anyone know where
this thing came from?

393
00:26:53,737 --> 00:26:55,113
This speaker?

394
00:26:55,196 --> 00:26:56,990
Huh? What's happening?

395
00:26:57,073 --> 00:27:00,619
It seems this doesn't belong
to the city hall or the vendor.

396
00:27:00,702 --> 00:27:02,871
-What?
-That's so strange.

397
00:27:02,954 --> 00:27:04,414
This belongs to the church.

398
00:27:09,002 --> 00:27:09,961
Hey.

399
00:27:11,046 --> 00:27:12,088
Are you okay?

400
00:27:15,008 --> 00:27:16,009
Father.

401
00:27:17,969 --> 00:27:19,387
What happened?

402
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:20,805
How are you feeling now?

403
00:27:22,390 --> 00:27:23,975
Everyone was so worried.

404
00:27:24,726 --> 00:27:27,687
You're the only priest now.
We can't have you dying on us.

405
00:27:27,771 --> 00:27:30,065
Why would you say that?

406
00:27:30,940 --> 00:27:33,318
-Ah! Wait, wait!
-That's not what I meant.

407
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:37,155
I'm just relieved he's okay is all.

408
00:27:39,908 --> 00:27:41,868
-You okay?
-I'm fine.

409
00:27:41,951 --> 00:27:43,370
-Here, Father.
-Ah!

410
00:27:43,453 --> 00:27:45,538
Thank you.

411
00:27:48,083 --> 00:27:50,168
Hey, In-a. Excuse me.

412
00:27:53,546 --> 00:27:54,464
Have some water.

413
00:27:54,547 --> 00:27:55,757
Ah, okay.

414
00:28:02,305 --> 00:28:04,224
When this church was built,

415
00:28:04,933 --> 00:28:08,978
your grandparents
gave a… rather large offering.

416
00:28:10,522 --> 00:28:12,315
And that's when they told me

417
00:28:13,274 --> 00:28:14,943
they hoped one of their grandsons

418
00:28:15,735 --> 00:28:17,487
would become a priest someday.

419
00:28:18,571 --> 00:28:20,699
So I told them not to worry about it

420
00:28:20,782 --> 00:28:25,578
and to send the youngest of the three,
Sung-jae, to seminary.

421
00:28:31,084 --> 00:28:32,085
Why?

422
00:28:33,294 --> 00:28:34,504
Why choose me, Father?

423
00:28:35,922 --> 00:28:37,966
Samuel said unto Jesse,

424
00:28:38,925 --> 00:28:40,927
"Are these all the sons you have?"

425
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,263
And Jesse answered,

426
00:28:43,346 --> 00:28:45,140
"There is still the youngest."

427
00:28:45,223 --> 00:28:47,392
"He is out tending to the sheep."

428
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:50,729
Samuel told them to send for him.

429
00:28:51,229 --> 00:28:54,691
And when he came,
the man was the picture of health.

430
00:28:54,774 --> 00:28:56,359
A fine appearance as well.

431
00:28:56,443 --> 00:28:59,279
And, of course, handsome features.

432
00:29:01,114 --> 00:29:02,699
"Fallen at last"!

433
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,535
"Fallen at last"!

434
00:29:06,661 --> 00:29:09,372
"Fallen is Babylon the Great"!

435
00:29:10,039 --> 00:29:11,166
"Fallen at last"!

436
00:29:14,169 --> 00:29:17,005
"Fallen at last is Babylon the Great"!

437
00:29:17,797 --> 00:29:20,216
They ate everything we had.

438
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:23,178
People need to see
that kind of organization fall

439
00:29:23,261 --> 00:29:25,013
to know that the world is changing.

440
00:29:28,141 --> 00:29:30,727
Humans are foolish, after all.

441
00:29:30,810 --> 00:29:32,353
Dad, this is not okay.

442
00:29:32,437 --> 00:29:34,689
The guys need to bring
their own food from now on.

443
00:29:34,773 --> 00:29:36,524
It's our duty to share what we can.

444
00:29:36,608 --> 00:29:37,817
Are you kidding me right now?

445
00:29:37,901 --> 00:29:40,653
A parent should first make sure
that their kid doesn't starve.

446
00:29:41,654 --> 00:29:42,989
Jin-seo.

447
00:29:43,072 --> 00:29:45,283
Let me tell you about the welfare state.

448
00:29:45,366 --> 00:29:46,534
They never--

449
00:29:50,955 --> 00:29:52,749
You're letting mosquitoes in.

450
00:29:55,001 --> 00:29:56,419
I'm so hungry.

451
00:30:08,932 --> 00:30:10,683
I can't stand it.

452
00:30:12,227 --> 00:30:14,187
Can you imagine anything worse?

453
00:30:15,021 --> 00:30:17,440
All of that money vanished into thin air.

454
00:30:18,107 --> 00:30:20,026
Can you please stop that?

455
00:30:20,109 --> 00:30:22,695
He would say,
"Teresa, your faith is unmatched."

456
00:30:22,779 --> 00:30:24,405
"Teresa, what a saint you are."

457
00:30:24,489 --> 00:30:27,492
Ma, what's the point
of having money right now?

458
00:30:29,619 --> 00:30:30,537
The point?

459
00:30:31,371 --> 00:30:32,247
Hey.

460
00:30:33,498 --> 00:30:36,084
It's not the money that's important.
It's the fact that it's gone.

461
00:30:36,167 --> 00:30:37,168
What do you mean?

462
00:30:37,252 --> 00:30:38,878
If all the gold is gone,

463
00:30:39,963 --> 00:30:41,297
that means Father Baek

464
00:30:42,048 --> 00:30:43,299
left with everything.

465
00:30:44,634 --> 00:30:45,885
How could he do this?

466
00:30:47,136 --> 00:30:48,763
He abandoned all of us,

467
00:30:49,264 --> 00:30:52,100
his many followers,
all of us so blind in our faith.

468
00:30:52,183 --> 00:30:54,060
How could he just leave us like this?

469
00:30:55,061 --> 00:30:57,856
-It's too awful. Too awful to believe.
-Hey, you're on my foot.

470
00:30:59,148 --> 00:31:01,734
Why did it have to happen to me?

471
00:31:04,696 --> 00:31:08,241
The world is ending soon,
but it's trying to end me first.

472
00:31:10,034 --> 00:31:11,160
Ha-neul!

473
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:14,998
Where are you?

474
00:31:18,084 --> 00:31:19,669
You have to come home!

475
00:31:47,739 --> 00:31:49,866
Goodness! What a day.

476
00:31:51,075 --> 00:31:52,118
I know.

477
00:31:53,661 --> 00:31:54,704
Are you headed out?

478
00:31:55,246 --> 00:31:57,707
No.
I'm waiting for In-a and Yun-sang.

479
00:31:58,291 --> 00:32:00,752
Captain Kang? Where did she go?

480
00:32:01,294 --> 00:32:03,838
She went to city hall
to check some sound equipment.

481
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:04,923
Ah.

482
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:08,635
Oh! Hey.

483
00:32:08,718 --> 00:32:10,094
All right, here we go.

484
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:13,890
Oh, Sister.
I had something I wanted to ask you.

485
00:32:14,974 --> 00:32:17,518
Do you know if this speaker
belongs to the church?

486
00:32:18,019 --> 00:32:19,687
Yeah. It does, doesn't it?

487
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:22,357
-It does?
-Uh… Oh! I think so?

488
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:24,275
Earlier this morning, Sister and I put--

489
00:32:24,359 --> 00:32:26,569
Oops, I guess I just forgot!
Thanks so much.

490
00:32:26,653 --> 00:32:29,072
I noticed
this thing has Bluetooth.

491
00:32:30,156 --> 00:32:32,909
So they probably used that earlier today

492
00:32:33,993 --> 00:32:35,161
to connect to it.

493
00:32:36,579 --> 00:32:38,206
So that's how it happened?

494
00:32:39,082 --> 00:32:40,041
I think so.

495
00:32:40,124 --> 00:32:42,752
How else would they
have taken over the sound system?

496
00:32:44,253 --> 00:32:45,171
Sister.

497
00:32:45,922 --> 00:32:48,091
Sorry, but may I see your phone.

498
00:32:48,883 --> 00:32:49,759
My phone?

499
00:32:49,842 --> 00:32:50,969
Yes.

500
00:32:52,011 --> 00:32:53,096
My phone?

501
00:32:53,721 --> 00:32:54,681
Um…

502
00:33:06,859 --> 00:33:08,403
Okay, it was me.

503
00:33:09,028 --> 00:33:10,279
Fine, I put it there!

504
00:33:16,536 --> 00:33:19,038
Then… whose voice was it?

505
00:33:19,122 --> 00:33:20,415
I'm not at liberty to say.

506
00:33:20,498 --> 00:33:21,624
Sister.

507
00:33:33,678 --> 00:33:35,680
All right, then. I suppose I must speak.

508
00:33:37,849 --> 00:33:38,808
Think about it.

509
00:33:39,767 --> 00:33:41,436
The church extension funds.

510
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:43,396
Where'd all that money come from, huh?

511
00:33:44,188 --> 00:33:46,816
