Oh! Did I splash on you?

760
00:49:38,475 --> 00:49:40,727
Oh, I did. I'm so sorry.

761
00:49:41,979 --> 00:49:43,605
You still feeling down?

762
00:49:43,689 --> 00:49:44,898
Sister!

763
00:49:46,149 --> 00:49:48,276
Why don't you start the group meal?

764
00:49:48,360 --> 00:49:50,070
Don't just stand there confused.

765
00:49:50,153 --> 00:49:52,155
Go about your duties
as you've always done.

766
00:49:53,740 --> 00:49:55,826
Yeah, I can do that.

767
00:49:55,909 --> 00:49:59,079
All right, then.
Move along! Off you go!

768
00:50:05,252 --> 00:50:08,422
I mean, are you all right, huh?
What can I do?

769
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:14,302
Let me take care of this.
I've got it.

770
00:50:14,928 --> 00:50:16,847
Oh my, there's so much work.

771
00:50:16,930 --> 00:50:19,433
-Do you youngsters need a break?
-No, sir!

772
00:50:20,684 --> 00:50:22,811
Would you look at that?

773
00:50:23,562 --> 00:50:25,188
Yes, Bishop, this is Father Woo.

774
00:50:26,898 --> 00:50:27,774
Yes.

775
00:50:31,111 --> 00:50:32,446
They ruled it an accident.

776
00:50:35,157 --> 00:50:36,074
Yes, yes.

777
00:50:38,535 --> 00:50:39,578
Ah, yes, of course.

778
00:50:41,413 --> 00:50:42,372
Yes, yes.

779
00:50:43,290 --> 00:50:45,125
Well, that's good, I suppose.

780
00:50:45,208 --> 00:50:47,127
I'm glad it wasn't arson, at least.

781
00:50:47,711 --> 00:50:50,839
Well, since the insurance
isn't paying for it,

782
00:50:50,922 --> 00:50:53,216
it doesn't really matter
what caused the fire.

783
00:50:54,176 --> 00:50:56,845
The parish is gonna offer to help, right?

784
00:50:57,512 --> 00:50:58,638
Oh, of course.

785
00:50:58,722 --> 00:51:01,892
Just because Father Baek is gone
doesn't mean they'll forget us.

786
00:51:01,975 --> 00:51:05,103
Then, do you think the parish
has some kind of plan for us?

787
00:51:05,187 --> 00:51:06,480
Yeah, probably.

788
00:51:06,980 --> 00:51:09,024
Oh dear.
I don't know what to think anymore.

789
00:51:38,804 --> 00:51:41,098
-What's up?
-Is everything done?

790
00:51:41,181 --> 00:51:42,182
Mmm.

791
00:51:46,603 --> 00:51:47,938
What did the parish say?

792
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:51,274
Father Baek left. Now the fire too.

793
00:51:53,443 --> 00:51:54,736
They can't be happy.

794
00:51:56,446 --> 00:51:58,156
Still no answer.

795
00:51:59,699 --> 00:52:02,661
My guess is they want us
to take care of it on our own.

796
00:52:04,037 --> 00:52:06,289
So I'm thinking about what to do now.

797
00:52:07,874 --> 00:52:10,377
It's not like you can do it alone. Right?

798
00:52:10,460 --> 00:52:12,504
And you don't even know what's going on.

799
00:52:14,798 --> 00:52:16,049
You did look pretty cool earlier

800
00:52:16,133 --> 00:52:18,510
when you told that investigator
to back off and leave.

801
00:52:18,593 --> 00:52:20,428
-I did?
-Yeah, you did.

802
00:52:29,980 --> 00:52:31,439
Why do you think he left?

803
00:52:33,984 --> 00:52:35,819
How could he abandon us like this?

804
00:52:37,154 --> 00:52:39,948
There was something
that Father Baek used to say a lot.

805
00:52:42,993 --> 00:52:44,911
That we're always on our way to maturity.

806
00:52:46,204 --> 00:52:48,331
That makes no sense at all.

807
00:52:54,004 --> 00:52:55,172
Excuse me.

808
00:52:55,255 --> 00:52:58,133
-Would you like to eat first?
-No, let's eat together.

809
00:52:58,216 --> 00:52:59,718
-All right.
-Thank you.

810
00:53:36,087 --> 00:53:37,631
If I had to choose,

811
00:53:39,257 --> 00:53:41,676
I would spend every day we have left

812
00:53:43,011 --> 00:53:45,138
hunting each of those bastards down

813
00:53:47,307 --> 00:53:49,100
and punishing them for my son.

814
00:53:50,268 --> 00:53:52,020
I don't expect to be forgiven.

815
00:53:57,567 --> 00:53:58,860
With thoughts like that…

816
00:54:01,238 --> 00:54:03,657
I won't be able
to see Min-ho again, will I?

817
00:54:11,748 --> 00:54:13,083
Sister Christina.

818
00:54:17,420 --> 00:54:18,922
"Revenge is my job."

819
00:54:19,673 --> 00:54:21,508
"I will seek vengeance for you."

820
00:54:23,468 --> 00:54:25,387
That is what the Lord says to us.

821
00:54:48,285 --> 00:54:49,619
-I want a sausage!
-Dear Lord.

822
00:54:49,703 --> 00:54:51,413
We thank you for all the grace
you have given us.

823
00:54:51,496 --> 00:54:52,789
I want a sausage!

824
00:54:52,872 --> 00:54:54,249
Amen.

825
00:54:54,332 --> 00:54:56,126
I want a sausage! I want a sausage!

826
00:54:56,209 --> 00:54:59,170
Goodness me!
This little pup must be starving!

827
00:54:59,254 --> 00:55:01,548
-It's coming out. Thank you for the food.
-I want a sausage!

828
00:55:01,631 --> 00:55:02,966
Everyone enjoy.

829
00:55:03,550 --> 00:55:04,843
Enjoy your meal.

830
00:55:04,926 --> 00:55:08,596
Since you all worked hard today,
let's share a drink. One glass each.

831
00:55:09,973 --> 00:55:11,474
-Mmm.
-Where's unni, huh?

832
00:55:11,558 --> 00:55:14,019
Oh, uh, she said her stomach hurt
and went home.

833
00:55:14,102 --> 00:55:15,520
She told me to have dinner here.

834
00:55:15,603 --> 00:55:17,689
Wait, what? How did she get
an upset stomach?

835
00:55:17,772 --> 00:55:19,399
I don't know. She just said it hurt.

836
00:55:19,983 --> 00:55:22,193
Well, still,
it's not good to skip meals.

837
00:55:22,277 --> 00:55:24,654
-Is it good?
-She must be stressed out.

838
00:55:26,990 --> 00:55:29,576
Father,
so about the mass going forward…

839
00:56:18,333 --> 00:56:20,377
It's me. Se-kyung.

840
00:56:40,563 --> 00:56:43,233
Where did my drink go, unni?

841
00:56:44,567 --> 00:56:46,319
You said we'd drink this together.

842
00:56:49,531 --> 00:56:50,365
What?

843
00:56:51,116 --> 00:56:53,284
I just had one thing on my mind tonight.

844
00:56:53,368 --> 00:56:55,787
I walked home thinking about this drink.

845
00:56:56,329 --> 00:56:58,581
I thought we were
gonna have a glass together.

846
00:57:06,673 --> 00:57:08,591
Uh, what do I do now?

847
00:57:11,302 --> 00:57:12,929
-What to do.
-Here.

848
00:57:13,972 --> 00:57:15,306
I put yours aside.

849
00:57:21,187 --> 00:57:22,856
You had it ready.

850
00:57:22,939 --> 00:57:24,023
Thanks, unni.

851
00:57:34,409 --> 00:57:35,952
Let's clear our minds for now.

852
00:57:38,371 --> 00:57:40,874
Together until the end.

853
00:57:41,833 --> 00:57:42,667
Hmm?

854
00:58:19,454 --> 00:58:21,289
It's really coming down.
